Name: B-actin
Definition: nonmuscle cytoskeletal actin,  involved in cell motility, structure and integrity

Name: CASP1
Definition: Caspase-1/Interleukin-1 converting enzyme is an evolutionarily conserved enzyme that proteolytically cleaves other proteins

Name: CD56
Function: CD56bright = more cytokine producing NKs, CD56dim = more direct cytotoxic killing
Definition: cell surface glycoprotein

Name: CDC42
Definition: protein involved in regulation of the cell cycle

Name: CXCL9
Function: immune cell migration marker + Th1 activator
Definition: binds to CXCR3 and primarily attracts activated T lymphocytes

Name: CXCR3
Definition: important role in T cell trafficking and function

Name: GAPDH
Definition: enzyme for energy metabolism and the production of ATP and pyruvate

Name: IDO1
Function: DC, monocyte and MC protein regulating T-cell activity
Definition: capable of modulating immune cell activation status and phenotype

Name: IFNy
Function: compare with IFN-y producing cells and IFN-y ELISAs, should correlate wit PRF1, NKp46 and F4/80. One of these cell types just have to be doing the job!
Definition: important activator of macrophages and inducer of major histocompatibility complex class II molecule expression

Name: IL-10
Definition: cytokine synthesis inhibitory factor, an anti-inflammatory cytokine

Name: IL-12ra
Definition: effective in combatting a wide range of naturally occurring viral infections through the upregulation of various cytokines

Name: IL-13
Definition: produced by Th2 cells, natural killer T cell

Name: IL-17
Function: in case IFN-y isn't coming up but pathogenicity is
Definition: pro-inflammatory cystine knot cytokine

Name: IL-1Ra
Function: natuaral IL-1b antagonist for infection control (if not increase in Tregs is seen)

Name: IL-4
Definition: induces differentiation of naive helper T cells to Th2 cells

Name: IL-6
Definition: acts as both a pro-inflammatory cytokine and an anti-inflammatory myokine

Name: IRG6A
Definition: antibody that plays a crucial role in the immune function of mucous membranes

Name: Mpo
Definition: most abundantly expressed in neutrophil granulocytes, and produces hypohalous acids to carry out their antimicrobial activit

Name: Muc2
Function: the major secretory mucin within the gastrointestinal tract
Definition: Coats the epithelia of the intestines, airways, and other mucus membrane-containing organs

Name: Muc5ac
Function: similar to MUC2, produced by surface goblet cells
Definition: Gel-forming glycoprotein of gastric and respiratory tract epithelia

Name: MyD88
Function: TLR protein, NF-kB IRAK protein, inflammation marker by TLR
Definition: canonical adaptor for inflammatory signaling pathways downstream of members of the Toll-like receptor (TLR) and interleukin-1 (IL-1) receptor families

Name: NKp46
Definition: innate lymphocytes that efficiently eliminate cancerous and infected cells

Name: PPIA
Definition: catalyzes the cis-trans isomerization of proline imidic peptide bonds, which allows it to regulate many biological processes, including intracellular signaling, transcription, inflammation, and apoptosis

Name: PPIB
Definition: catalyzes the cis-trans isomerization of proline imidic peptide bonds, which allows it to regulate protein folding of type I collagen

Name: Prf1
Function: perforin, should be dominant in primary infections, but must be correlated between T-cell and NK cell expresions
Definition: Pore-forming protein that plays a key role in secretory granule-dependent cell death, and in defense against virus-infected or neoplastic cells

Name: Relm-b
Definition: cysteine-rich cytokine expressed in the gastrointestinal tract and implicated in insulin resistance and gastrointestinal nematode immunity

Name: Socs1
Function: JAK/STAT signaling pathway, proinflammatory regulating + T-cell differentiation, could explain severity
Definition: SOCS-1 regulates responses to IL-12 in mice

Name: TFF3
Definition: stable secretory protein expressed in the goblet cells of the gastrointestinal mucosa

Name: TNF-a
Function: upregulated in eimeria but not well explained. Could be present and driving infection where IFN-y isn't
Definition: inflammatory cytokine produced by macrophages/monocytes during acute inflammation

Name: TRIF
Definition: cytosolic adaptor protein, plays a key role in the mammalian toll-like receptor-mediated signaling pathway
